The paper deals with the extension of prime implicates and prime implicants from propositional logic to modal logic, which is a topic relevant to several areas of artificial intelligence. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses syntactic, semantic, and complexity-theoretic properties of different definitions of clauses and terms for modal logic, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper examines the computational properties of the selected definition, which could be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper mentions that its results hold for concept expressions in the description logic ALC, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
